<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7676&amp;p=33027#p33027"><![CDATA[
Hi guys!<br /><br />I'm on Windows 10 Anniversary Edition 64-bit, and there's an issue with the Classic Start Menu. I use the auto-hide feature for the taskbar. I generally don't have any problem. However, sometimes, after using the Classic Start Menu, the task bar won't hide, even after opening it again, clicking on windows, etc. The only way to correct this is to open the Windows 10 Start Menu and close it.<br />It doesn't happen that often so I haven't figured out what could be the cause of this behaviour.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=11296">Joey79100</a> — Thu Jun 15, 2017 10:52 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
